Merlai - AI-powered music creation assistant

PRODUCT DESIGN & ARCHITECTURE:
Copyright 2025 Yoshitake Asano
GitHub: https://github.com/yoshitake945
- Product concept and vision
- System architecture design
- Technology stack selection
- User experience design
- Project management and direction

IMPLEMENTATION:
AI-Assisted Development
- Code implementation by AI coding assistants
- Technical documentation by AI tools
- Library integration and API design
- Testing and quality assurance

AI DEVELOPMENT TOOLS USED:
Primary Development Environment:
- Cursor (AI-powered code editor)
  - Built on VS Code with integrated AI assistance
  - Used for real-time code generation and editing
  - Provided context-aware suggestions and completions

AI Models and Services:
- OpenAI GPT-4 (via Cursor integration)
  - Primary AI model for code generation
  - Used for architecture design and implementation
  - Assisted with documentation and testing
- OpenAI ChatGPT
  - Used for initial idea brainstorming and concept development
  - Assisted with product vision and feature planning
  - Provided creative input for user experience design
- GitHub Copilot (when available)
  - Secondary AI assistance for code completion
  - Used for routine coding tasks and suggestions

Future AI Tools:
This project may incorporate additional AI tools and services as they become
available. The development approach embraces continuous integration of new
AI capabilities to enhance productivity and code quality.

Development Process:
- Initial concept development with ChatGPT
- Iterative AI-assisted development with Cursor + GPT-4
- Human review and refinement of AI-generated code
- Continuous improvement through AI feedback loops
- Collaborative development between human and AI
- Ongoing integration of new AI tools and capabilities

This product includes software developed by:
- Yoshitake Asano (Product Design & Architecture)
  - GitHub: https://github.com/yoshitake945
- AI Coding Assistants (Implementation via Cursor + GPT-4)
- AI Creative Assistants (Ideation via ChatGPT)

